{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EK7xjE1LUgkbyPCUx8x8zN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Codex Review -- 20260423-1145\n2\t## Models: GPT-5.3-codex + GPT-5.4\n3\t\n4\t## Verdict: FAIL\n5\t\n6\tReason: 1 Critical finding (1M model detection broken for new model IDs) and 2 Major findings.\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Findings\n11\t\n12\t### [Critical] 1M model detection broken for new model IDs [5.3+5.4]\n13\t- **File**: src/components/chat/ChatPanel.tsx:258\n14\t- **File**: src-tauri/src/lib.rs:1472\n15\t- **Problem**: The commit adds 4 new model IDs (`claude-opus-4-7-1m`, `claude-opus-4-6-1m`,\n16\t  `claude-opus-4-6`, `claude-opus-4-7`) but the 1M context detection logic does NOT recognize\n17\t  the new `-1m` suffix pattern. Frontend checks `resolvedModel.includes('[1m]')` (square brackets,\n18\t  not dash) and `selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'` (only one model). Rust backend checks\n19\t  `m.contains(\"[1m]\")` (square brackets again).\n20\t- **Evidence**:\n21\t  - ChatPanel.tsx:258: `const is1MModel = resolvedModel.includes('[1m]') || selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'`\n22\t  - lib.rs:1472: `if m.contains(\"mimo\") || m.contains(\"[1m]\")`\n23\t  - New IDs use `-1m` suffix (e.g. `claude-opus-4-7-1m`), not `[1m]`\n24\t- **Consequences**:\n25\t  1. Frontend context pressure warning triggers at 120K (60% of 200K) instead of 600K for\n26\t     1M models -- spurious warnings\n27\t  2. Rust backend does NOT set `CLAUDE_CODE_AUTO_COMPACT_WINDOW=1000000` for `-1m` models,\n28\t     potentially causing premature auto-compaction\n29\t  3. `claude-opus-4-6` and `claude-opus-4-6-1m` are not detected as 1M models at all\n30\t- **Fix**: Unify 1M model detection into a helper function. At minimum:\n31\t  - Frontend: `selectedModel.endsWith('-1m') || selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'`\n32\t  - Rust: `m.ends_with(\"-1m\") || m == \"claude-opus-4-7\"` (in addition to existing mimo/[1m] checks)\n33\t  - Better: add `is1M: boolean` to `MODEL_OPTIONS` metadata and derive from there\n34\t\n35\t### [Major] Interaction card blocking loses file attachments and prefix [5.3+5.4]\n36\t- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:771 (clearFiles) vs 793-797 (return with rawInput only)\n37\t- **Problem**: When an unresolved interaction card blocks queueing, the code path at line 793-797\n38\t  restores only `rawInput` to the input draft. But by this point, `clearFiles()` at line 771\n39\t  has already destroyed the file attachments, and `clearPrefix()` at line 706 has consumed the\n40\t  command prefix. The user loses their attachments silently.\n41\t- **Evidence**: Sequential code flow:\n42\t  - Line 706: `useCommandStore.getState().clearPrefix()` -- prefix consumed\n43\t  - Line 771: `clearFiles()` -- attachments destroyed\n44\t  - Line 793-797: only `rawInput` is restored, no attachment/prefix recovery\n45\t- **Fix**: Move the interaction-card check before `clearFiles()` (and ideally before\n46\t  `clearPrefix()`), or restore attachments and prefix on the blocking return path.\n47\t\n48\t### [Major] spawnConfigHash computed after async spawn -- race with user config changes [5.4]\n49\t- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:1071\n50\t- **File**: src/components/chat/ChatPanel.tsx:849\n51\t- **File**: src/hooks/useStreamProcessor.ts:1710\n52\t- **Problem**: `spawnConfigHash()` is called AFTER `await spawnSession(...)` completes, reading\n53\t  current store state rather than the config that was actually used to spawn the process. If the\n54\t  user changes model/provider/thinking during the async spawn (1-3 seconds), the stored hash\n55\t  reflects the NEW config, not what the process was spawned with. Next handleSubmit would see\n56\t  matching hashes and skip the necessary respawn.\n57\t- **Evidence**: Spawn parameters are captured at lines 1035-1055 (before await), but the hash\n58\t  at line 1071 reads fresh from the store after await. The hash function reads\n59\t  `useSettingsStore.getState()` and `useProviderStore.getState()` at call time.\n60\t- **Fix**: Compute `spawnConfigHash()` BEFORE the await (alongside other config captures at\n61\t  lines 1035-1055), and use the pre-computed value when writing sessionMeta after spawn succeeds.\n62\t  Alternatively, make `spawnConfigHash` accept explicit parameters instead of reading from store.\n63\t\n64\t### [Minor] enqueueStdinId captured but never validated in drain paths [5.3-codex]\n65\t- **File**: src/stores/chatStore.ts:195 (field defined)\n66\t- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:801 (captured at enqueue)\n67\t- **File**: src/hooks/useStreamProcessor.ts:607,1953 (drain paths -- no check)\n68\t- **Problem**: `enqueueStdinId` is stored on each queued message but never compared against the\n69\t  current session's stdinId during drain. The docstring at chatStore.ts:186 says it exists \"so\n70\t  the drain path can detect config drift,\" but it is dead metadata.\n71\t- **Evidence**: Grep for `enqueueStdinId` shows 5 hits: 2 type definitions, 1 capture, 1 store,\n72\t  0 reads in drain logic.\n73\t- **Fix**: Either use it (compare `p.enqueueStdinId !== bgFlushStdinId` during drain as an\n74\t  additional safety check) or remove the field to avoid confusion. Using it would close the\n75\t  theoretical gap where config changes between enqueue and drain are not detected because the\n76\t  global hash hasn't changed yet.\n77\t\n78\t### [Minor] ModelSelector shows identical labels for all 4 opus variants when provider is active [5.4]\n79\t- **File**: src/components/chat/ModelSelector.tsx:64-67\n80\t- **Problem**: When an active provider is configured, all 4 opus variants (4.6, 4.6-1m, 4.7,\n81\t  4.7-1m) map to the same tier \"opus\" and display the same provider model name (e.g., \"glm-5\").\n82\t  Users cannot distinguish between them in the dropdown.\n83\t- **Evidence**: TIER_MAP maps all 4 opus IDs to 'opus'. Line 62-67 replaces the label with the\n84\t  provider model name, losing the original variant distinction.\n85\t- **Note**: This is a pre-existing design choice (line 59 comment: \"keep both entries with their\n86\t  original labels\") but the comment contradicts the implementation at line 67. Adding 4 opus\n87\t  variants makes it worse.\n88\t- **Fix**: Preserve the original MODEL_OPTIONS label as primary, show provider model as secondary\n89\t  text. Or append variant info: \"glm-5 (Opus 4.7)\" vs \"glm-5 (Opus 4.6 1M)\".\n90\t\n91\t### [Minor] Spawn failure does not restore user message to inputDraft (PRD gap) [5.4]\n92\t- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:810-817 (addMessage) vs 1082-1092 (catch)\n93\t- **Problem**: The user's message is added to chat history at line 810 before spawn. If spawn\n94\t  fails, the catch block sets error status and adds an error system message, but does not\n95\t  restore the user's text to inputDraft. The user's message appears \"sent\" but was never processed.\n96\t  PRD line 102-103 requires \"消息回填 inputDraft + 显示错误文案\".\n97\t- **Evidence**: catch block at 1082-1092 has no `setInputDraft` call.\n98\t- **Note**: This is a pre-existing behavior, not introduced by this commit. But the PRD\n99\t  explicitly calls it out as a requirement for Task B.\n100\t- **Fix**: In the catch block, restore the original rawInput to inputDraft and optionally remove\n101\t  the user message bubble that was already added.\n102\t\n103\t---\n104\t\n105\t## Review Coverage\n106\t- **Checked**: All 12 changed files line-by-line; cross-file call chains for spawnConfigHash\n107\t  (6 write sites, 3 read sites); drain paths in useStreamProcessor (foreground + background);\n108\t  Rust bypass runtime wiring (BypassModeMap register/set_bypass/drop_if_current -- confirmed\n109\t  already implemented in Task A); 1M model detection in both frontend and Rust backend;\n110\t  PendingUserMessage type migration across all consumers; v7 migration removal safety;\n111\t  settingsStore subscribe watcher; TypeScript compilation (passes).\n112\t- **Not checked**: Vitest execution (sandbox EPERM on .vite-temp); Rust cargo check/clippy\n113\t  (no Rust changes in this commit, verified existing code only); end-to-end interaction card\n114\t  blocking flow; actual CLI behavior with new model IDs (depends on CLI version).\n115\t- **Bypass runtime (S14)**: Confirmed fully wired in Task A commit af59118. No Rust changes\n116\t  needed in this commit. BypassModeMap register at spawn, AtomicBool read in stdout loop,\n117\t  set_bypass on set_permission_mode, cleanup on process exit -- all present and correct.\n118\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dcb2e38-d9a0-456f-a0b4-50bcd29e86c0","uuid":"48df9f37-a80f-4cc1-8fcb-e48d19ee4701","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:47:21.989Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/suyuan/Documents/her-source/trellis-worktrees/fix/task-B-config-switching/.trellis/tasks/04-22-B-config-switching/codex-review-20260423-1145.txt","content":"# Codex Review -- 20260423-1145\n## Models: GPT-5.3-codex + GPT-5.4\n\n## Verdict: FAIL\n\nReason: 1 Critical finding (1M model detection broken for new model IDs) and 2 Major findings.\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### [Critical] 1M model detection broken for new model IDs [5.3+5.4]\n- **File**: src/components/chat/ChatPanel.tsx:258\n- **File**: src-tauri/src/lib.rs:1472\n- **Problem**: The commit adds 4 new model IDs (`claude-opus-4-7-1m`, `claude-opus-4-6-1m`,\n  `claude-opus-4-6`, `claude-opus-4-7`) but the 1M context detection logic does NOT recognize\n  the new `-1m` suffix pattern. Frontend checks `resolvedModel.includes('[1m]')` (square brackets,\n  not dash) and `selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'` (only one model). Rust backend checks\n  `m.contains(\"[1m]\")` (square brackets again).\n- **Evidence**:\n  - ChatPanel.tsx:258: `const is1MModel = resolvedModel.includes('[1m]') || selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'`\n  - lib.rs:1472: `if m.contains(\"mimo\") || m.contains(\"[1m]\")`\n  - New IDs use `-1m` suffix (e.g. `claude-opus-4-7-1m`), not `[1m]`\n- **Consequences**:\n  1. Frontend context pressure warning triggers at 120K (60% of 200K) instead of 600K for\n     1M models -- spurious warnings\n  2. Rust backend does NOT set `CLAUDE_CODE_AUTO_COMPACT_WINDOW=1000000` for `-1m` models,\n     potentially causing premature auto-compaction\n  3. `claude-opus-4-6` and `claude-opus-4-6-1m` are not detected as 1M models at all\n- **Fix**: Unify 1M model detection into a helper function. At minimum:\n  - Frontend: `selectedModel.endsWith('-1m') || selectedModel === 'claude-opus-4-7'`\n  - Rust: `m.ends_with(\"-1m\") || m == \"claude-opus-4-7\"` (in addition to existing mimo/[1m] checks)\n  - Better: add `is1M: boolean` to `MODEL_OPTIONS` metadata and derive from there\n\n### [Major] Interaction card blocking loses file attachments and prefix [5.3+5.4]\n- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:771 (clearFiles) vs 793-797 (return with rawInput only)\n- **Problem**: When an unresolved interaction card blocks queueing, the code path at line 793-797\n  restores only `rawInput` to the input draft. But by this point, `clearFiles()` at line 771\n  has already destroyed the file attachments, and `clearPrefix()` at line 706 has consumed the\n  command prefix. The user loses their attachments silently.\n- **Evidence**: Sequential code flow:\n  - Line 706: `useCommandStore.getState().clearPrefix()` -- prefix consumed\n  - Line 771: `clearFiles()` -- attachments destroyed\n  - Line 793-797: only `rawInput` is restored, no attachment/prefix recovery\n- **Fix**: Move the interaction-card check before `clearFiles()` (and ideally before\n  `clearPrefix()`), or restore attachments and prefix on the blocking return path.\n\n### [Major] spawnConfigHash computed after async spawn -- race with user config changes [5.4]\n- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:1071\n- **File**: src/components/chat/ChatPanel.tsx:849\n- **File**: src/hooks/useStreamProcessor.ts:1710\n- **Problem**: `spawnConfigHash()` is called AFTER `await spawnSession(...)` completes, reading\n  current store state rather than the config that was actually used to spawn the process. If the\n  user changes model/provider/thinking during the async spawn (1-3 seconds), the stored hash\n  reflects the NEW config, not what the process was spawned with. Next handleSubmit would see\n  matching hashes and skip the necessary respawn.\n- **Evidence**: Spawn parameters are captured at lines 1035-1055 (before await), but the hash\n  at line 1071 reads fresh from the store after await. The hash function reads\n  `useSettingsStore.getState()` and `useProviderStore.getState()` at call time.\n- **Fix**: Compute `spawnConfigHash()` BEFORE the await (alongside other config captures at\n  lines 1035-1055), and use the pre-computed value when writing sessionMeta after spawn succeeds.\n  Alternatively, make `spawnConfigHash` accept explicit parameters instead of reading from store.\n\n### [Minor] enqueueStdinId captured but never validated in drain paths [5.3-codex]\n- **File**: src/stores/chatStore.ts:195 (field defined)\n- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:801 (captured at enqueue)\n- **File**: src/hooks/useStreamProcessor.ts:607,1953 (drain paths -- no check)\n- **Problem**: `enqueueStdinId` is stored on each queued message but never compared against the\n  current session's stdinId during drain. The docstring at chatStore.ts:186 says it exists \"so\n  the drain path can detect config drift,\" but it is dead metadata.\n- **Evidence**: Grep for `enqueueStdinId` shows 5 hits: 2 type definitions, 1 capture, 1 store,\n  0 reads in drain logic.\n- **Fix**: Either use it (compare `p.enqueueStdinId !== bgFlushStdinId` during drain as an\n  additional safety check) or remove the field to avoid confusion. Using it would close the\n  theoretical gap where config changes between enqueue and drain are not detected because the\n  global hash hasn't changed yet.\n\n### [Minor] ModelSelector shows identical labels for all 4 opus variants when provider is active [5.4]\n- **File**: src/components/chat/ModelSelector.tsx:64-67\n- **Problem**: When an active provider is configured, all 4 opus variants (4.6, 4.6-1m, 4.7,\n  4.7-1m) map to the same tier \"opus\" and display the same provider model name (e.g., \"glm-5\").\n  Users cannot distinguish between them in the dropdown.\n- **Evidence**: TIER_MAP maps all 4 opus IDs to 'opus'. Line 62-67 replaces the label with the\n  provider model name, losing the original variant distinction.\n- **Note**: This is a pre-existing design choice (line 59 comment: \"keep both entries with their\n  original labels\") but the comment contradicts the implementation at line 67. Adding 4 opus\n  variants makes it worse.\n- **Fix**: Preserve the original MODEL_OPTIONS label as primary, show provider model as secondary\n  text. Or append variant info: \"glm-5 (Opus 4.7)\" vs \"glm-5 (Opus 4.6 1M)\".\n\n### [Minor] Spawn failure does not restore user message to inputDraft (PRD gap) [5.4]\n- **File**: src/components/chat/InputBar.tsx:810-817 (addMessage) vs 1082-1092 (catch)\n- **Problem**: The user's message is added to chat history at line 810 before spawn. If spawn\n  fails, the catch block sets error status and adds an error system message, but does not\n  restore the user's text to inputDraft. The user's message appears \"sent\" but was never processed.\n  PRD line 102-103 requires \"消息回填 inputDraft + 显示错误文案\".\n- **Evidence**: catch block at 1082-1092 has no `setInputDraft` call.\n- **Note**: This is a pre-existing behavior, not introduced by this commit. But the PRD\n  explicitly calls it out as a requirement for Task B.\n- **Fix**: In the catch block, restore the original rawInput to inputDraft and optionally remove\n  the user message bubble that was already added.\n\n---\n\n## Review Coverage\n- **Checked**: All 12 changed files line-by-line; cross-file call chains for spawnConfigHash\n  (6 write sites, 3 read sites); drain paths in useStreamProcessor (foreground + background);\n  Rust bypass runtime wiring (BypassModeMap register/set_bypass/drop_if_current -- confirmed\n  already implemented in Task A); 1M model detection in both frontend and Rust backend;\n  PendingUserMessage type migration across all consumers; v7 migration removal safety;\n  settingsStore subscribe watcher; TypeScript compilation (passes).\n- **Not checked**: Vitest execution (sandbox EPERM on .vite-temp); Rust cargo check/clippy\n  (no Rust changes in this commit, verified existing code only); end-to-end interaction card\n  blocking flow; actual CLI behavior with new model IDs (depends on CLI version).\n- **Bypass runtime (S14)**: Confirmed fully wired in Task A commit af59118. No Rust changes\n  needed in this commit. BypassModeMap register at spawn, AtomicBool read in stdout loop,\n  set_bypass on set_permission_mode, cleanup on process exit -- all present and correct.\n","numLines":118,"startLine":1,"totalLines":118}}}
