{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YEA3CckYwoTFBFTB4B2qz6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The verdict is \"PASS WITH NOTES\", but there are 3 Major findings. Per the protocol, \"PASS WITH NOTES without Critical/Major\" would be a clean pass. Since there ARE Major findings, I should technically treat this as needing another debug round.\n\nHowever, looking at the description of the findings:\n1. Pre-warm spawn hash race - same pattern already fixed in InputBar, lower risk\n2. Auto-retry spawn hash race - same pattern, moderate risk\n3. Spawn failure loses file attachments - early validation returns lose files\n\nThese are all described as \"variations of the same async-hash-race pattern\" and \"straightforward to fix\" and \"none represent Critical-level bugs (no data corruption, no security issues, no session breakage in the primary user flow).\"\n\n\nSince the protocol requires PASS WITH NOTES to be free of Major findings, I'll dispatch a debug agent now to address these 3 Major issues plus the 2 Minor ones, then run a final validation round.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":160,"cache_read_input_tokens":86273,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":160},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dcb2e38-d9a0-456f-a0b4-50bcd29e86c0","uuid":"1de7a719-090d-490d-a0cb-82d5b804b2eb"}
